  "prompt": "Where can I get Marvel comics free?",
  "response": "If you're looking to read Marvel comics for free, there are several legal and some not-so-legal options. Here are a few ways to explore:\n\n---\n\n### **Legal Ways to Read Marvel Comics for Free**  \n1. **Marvel Unlimited Free Trial**  \n   - Marvel offers a 7-day free trial for **Marvel Unlimited**, their digital comic subscription service. This gives you access to thousands of comics, including classic and modern titles.  \n   - Website: [https://www.marvel.com/unlimited](https://www.marvel.com/unlimited)\n\n2. **Public Libraries**  \n   - Many public libraries offer free access to digital comics through services like **Hoopla** or **Libby**. You can borrow Marvel comics legally with a library card.  \n   - Check your local library's website for details.\n\n3. **Comixology Free Issues**  \n   - Amazon's Comixology occasionally offers free issues of Marvel comics as part of promotions or special events.  \n   - Website: [https://www.comixology.com](https://www.comixology.com)\n\n4. **Marvel's Official Website**  \n   - Marvel often releases **free first issues** of new series or special previews on their website.  \n   - Check: [https://www.marvel.com/comics](https://www.marvel.com/comics)\n\n5. **Free Comic Book Day (FCBD)**  \n   - Every year, Marvel participates in **Free Comic Book Day**, where you can pick up free comics at participating local comic book stores.  \n   - Event website: [https://www.freecomicbookday.com](https://www.freecomicbookday.com)\n\n---\n\n### **Caution About Illegal Sources**  \nWhile there are websites and platforms that offer pirated Marvel comics, these are **illegal** and unethical. They harm creators, publishers, and the industry as a whole. Always opt for legal methods to support the artists and writers who bring these stories to life.\n\nLet me know if you'd like more help!",
